  "prompt": "Does the 112 emergency number work in the USA?",
  "response": "No, the **112 emergency number does not work in the USA** as a universal emergency number. In the United States, the primary emergency number is **911**, which connects callers to police, fire, and medical services.\n\n**112** is widely recognized as an emergency number in **Europe** and many other parts of the world, and in some countries, it may redirect to the local emergency number (like 911 in the U.S.). However, in the U.S., calling 112 will not connect you to emergency services. Always use **911** when in the United States.",
